Definitions:
Globalization - The process of an organization or government developing global influence or operating on a global scale
Bourgeois - Describing a person who, through financial means, owns, or manages, the means of production or subsistence. (i.e Factory owners, Landlords, Shift supervisors)
Proletariat - A person working a job which has been homogenized through industrialization, or who can otherwise be easily replaced by management. (i.e Line cooks, nurses, assembly line workers, clerks, janitors)
Bourgeoisie - The class of the Bourgeois
Imperialism - Extending power and itnfluence through diplomatic or militaristic means
